  "prompt": "What are some shows like Ellen and Dr. Phil?",
  "response": "If you're looking for shows similar to \"The Ellen DeGeneres Show\" and \"Dr. Phil,\" you might enjoy the following programs, which feature a mix of celebrity interviews, human-interest stories, and expert advice:\n\n1. **The Oprah Winfrey Show** - A classic talk show hosted by Oprah Winfrey that covered a wide range of topics including self-help, health, celebrity interviews, and inspiring stories.\n\n2. **The Wendy Williams Show** - Hosted by Wendy Williams, this show features pop culture discussions, celebrity interviews, and audience interactions.\n\n3. **Live with Kelly and Mark** - Hosted by Kelly Ripa and Mark Consuelos, this morning talk show includes celebrity interviews, lifestyle segments, and audience participation.\n\n4. **The View** - A daytime talk show featuring a panel of women who discuss current events, politics, and personal stories, often with celebrity guests.\n\n5. **The Talk** - Similar to \"The View,\" this show features a group of hosts discussing various topics and interviewing celebrities.\n\n6. **Steve Harvey** - Hosted by comedian Steve Harvey, this show includes a mix of celebrity interviews, relationship advice, and personal stories.\n\n7. **Rachael Ray** - A lifestyle and cooking show hosted by celebrity chef Rachael Ray, featuring cooking demonstrations, celebrity interviews, and lifestyle tips.\n\n8. **Dr. Oz** - A health and wellness talk show hosted by Dr. Mehmet Oz, covering medical advice, wellness tips, and interviews with medical experts and celebrities.\n\n9. **Maury** - Hosted by Maury Povich, this show primarily focuses on resolving relationship and family disputes, often using lie detector tests and DNA tests.\n\n10. **The Kelly Clarkson Show** - Hosted by singer Kelly Clarkson, this show features celebrity interviews, musical performances, and human-interest stories.\n\nThese shows offer a variety of content that includes interviews, expert advice, and personal stories, much like \"The Ellen DeGeneres Show\" and \"Dr. Phil.\"",
